# Cloudflare Pages routing.
#
# Critical: a request for a missing build asset must NOT fall back to index.html.
# The SPA-style fallback serves index.html as a 200 text/html with a 4h
# Cache-Control, so a single miss during a deploy-propagation window gets cached
# at the edge — every later request for that hashed chunk then returns HTML, and
# the browser fails the module import with "Expected a JavaScript module but got
# text/html". Returning a real 404 instead keeps the response uncacheable-as-asset
# and lets the next request fetch the real chunk once it has propagated.
#
# This app has no client-side router, so there is no legitimate SPA fallback to
# preserve — only the real .html pages plus hashed /assets/*.
/assets/* /404.html 404
